built chapel for them,
helped find a cure for them,

00:39:33.531 --> 00:39:35.344
spend all of his life there.

00:39:35.344 --> 00:39:38.615
One morning he was pouring
a kettle of boiling water

00:39:38.615 --> 00:39:40.815
into a cup and the water
swirled out of there

00:39:40.815 --> 00:39:42.919
and fell onto his bare foot.

00:39:42.919 --> 00:39:47.031
It took him a moment to
realize he couldn't feel it.

00:39:47.031 --> 00:39:49.791
He was horrified as to
what that intimated.

00:39:49.791 --> 00:39:51.557
He took some more boiling water,

00:39:51.557 --> 00:39:55.011
put it gently onto the other
foot, and he couldn't feel it.

00:39:55.011 --> 00:39:56.839
He knew what had happened.

00:39:56.839 --> 00:40:00.195
That morning he began his
sermon in a different line.

00:40:00.195 --> 00:40:03.092
He always began by saying,
my fellow believers.

00:40:03.092 --> 00:40:07.259
That morning he began by
saying, my fellow lepers.

00:40:08.390 --> 00:40:10.355
He'd contracted leprosy.

00:40:10.355 --> 00:40:12.787
So as my wife and I
were being shown around

00:40:12.787 --> 00:40:14.957
with this story, I came to his grave,

00:40:14.957 --> 00:40:17.451
and I said to the man showing me around,

00:40:17.451 --> 00:40:19.535
"Damien is buried here."

00:40:19.535 --> 00:40:22.204
He said, "No sir, he was,
but the body was exhumed

00:40:22.204 --> 00:40:23.991
"and the Belgium government asked for him

00:40:23.991 --> 00:40:25.431
"to be brought back."

00:40:25.431 --> 00:40:26.839
I said, "Oh wow."

00:40:26.839 --> 00:40:28.147
He said, "Yup."

00:40:28.147 --> 00:40:30.739
He was a hero, but the people in Moloka'i,

00:40:30.739 --> 00:40:34.519
the people with leprosy, and
he taught them to realize

00:40:34.519 --> 00:40:37.533
they were not lepers, they
were people with leprosy.

00:40:37.533 --> 00:40:40.217
Even though he referred
to himself as a leper,

00:40:40.217 --> 00:40:43.431
he was referring to it
purposely as an outcast.

00:40:43.431 --> 00:40:46.832
He said you're not a leper,
you're a person with leprosy.

00:40:46.832 --> 00:40:49.735
Always give them the dignity
of their person hood,

00:40:49.735 --> 00:40:52.270
and so when they wanted the body back,

00:40:52.270 --> 00:40:53.861
the people there gathered together

00:40:53.861 --> 00:40:55.494
and wrote to the Belgium government,

00:40:55.494 --> 00:40:59.306
please, he loved us, this was his home.

00:40:59.306 --> 00:41:02.906
Don't take his body back
from here, but they insisted.

00:41:02.906 --> 00:41:04.794
So they finally said alright.

00:41:04.794 --> 00:41:09.222
Will you cut off that right
hand and bury it here?

00:41:09.222 --> 00:41:11.722
It's the hand that touched us.

00:41:14.468 --> 00:41:18.550
And today in Moloka'i, in
that grave is not his body,

00:41:18.550 --> 00:41:22.550
it's the hand that reached
out and touched them.

00:41:23.426 --> 00:41:25.570
Some time ago when I was being interviewed

00:41:25.570 --> 00:41:28.004
by India's leading newspaper, the Hindu,

00:41:28.004 --> 00:41:31.831
they were really quizzing me
on why I come there and speak,

00:41:31.831 --> 00:41:36.209
and then they found out the
charitable work we do there

00:41:36.209 --> 00:41:39.724
through my daughters work,
Wellspring International,

00:41:39.724 --> 00:41:42.496
and she looked at me and
said, you're doing this?

00:41:42.496 --> 00:41:44.916
I said, yeah we're home for the destitute.

00:41:44.916 --> 00:41:47.060
We work with prostitutes in the streets.

00:41:47.060 --> 00:41:50.149
We've got children with aids
that we work, and burn victims.

00:41:50.149 --> 00:41:52.084
Went through all of that.

00:41:52.084 --> 00:41:55.137
She looked at me and said to me,

00:41:55.137 --> 00:41:58.002
"I will ever be grateful
for what you're doing

00:41:58.002 --> 00:42:00.130
"for your mother land and your home land."

00:42:00.130 --> 00:42:01.918
The next day when she wrote the article,

00:42:01.918 --> 00:42:04.527
there was not one negative
word of criticism.

00:42:04.527 --> 00:42:07.268
It was just a series of appreciations

00:42:07.268 --> 00:42:09.802
of what was being done for the needy.

00:42:09.802 --> 00:42:12.969
You see, even the hostile are disarmed

00:42:14.754 --> 00:42:18.754
when they can see, and when
they can feel your touch.

00:42:18.754 --> 00:42:21.616
To you young people
especially I say to you,

00:42:21.616 --> 00:42:24.394
find some time in your college days,

00:42:24.394 --> 00:42:27.646
in your school days to go and
touch other peoples lives.

00:42:27.646 --> 00:42:31.022
It will be the most memorable
and the most wonderful thing

00:42:31.022 --> 00:42:35.413
you're ever doing, and do it
in the name of Jesus Christ.

00:42:35.413 --> 00:42:37.355
I'll give you a quick illustration.

00:42:37.355 --> 00:42:39.875
Time's running out but they
gave me a little more time

00:42:39.875 --> 00:42:40.958
that I could.

00:42:42.019 --> 00:42:45.614
In India, the washer
doesn't run, it walks.

00:42:45.614 --> 00:42:47.091
(laughing)

00:42:47.091 --> 00:42:48.841
But out here it runs.

00:42:50.408 --> 00:42:54.476
There's a guy in Delhi pushing himself.

00:42:54.476 --> 00:42:59.132
Only one leg bandaged up with
all horrible marks on it.

00:42:59.132 --> 00:43:00.648
I don't know what lay beneath it,

00:43:00.648 --> 00:43:03.079
but it was a horrible looking thing,

00:43:03.079 --> 00:43:05.359
and he had two stubs for arms.

00:43:05.359 --> 00:43:06.727
He was pulling himself.

00:43:06.727 --> 00:43:08.484
He did have one hand gnarled up,

00:43:08.484 --> 00:43:10.447
and I wanted to give him something,

00:43:10.447 --> 00:43:13.191
but I knew if I started
that I'd be crowded out.

00:43:13.191 --> 00:43:15.018
So I just followed him from a distance

00:43:15.018 --> 00:43:16.729
till there was not much of a crowd

00:43:16.729 --> 00:43:19.519
and as soon as I got close I said, bisob.

00:43:19.519 --> 00:43:22.234
(mumbles) means brother sir.

00:43:22.234 --> 00:43:23.763
I said, (speaking foreign language)

00:43:23.763 --> 00:43:25.203
can you wait for a moment?

00:43:25.203 --> 00:43:27.123
So I walked over to him and a knelt down

00:43:27.123 --> 00:43:29.163
on my haunches and I said to him,

00:43:29.163 --> 00:43:31.578
I want to give you this in
the name of Jesus Christ

00:43:31.578 --> 00:43:33.093
who loves you.

00:43:33.093 --> 00:43:34.655
It was 100 rupees.

00:43:34.655 --> 00:43:35.931
It was a lot for him.

00:43:35.931 --> 00:43:37.348
It's about $1.50.

00:43:38.479 --> 00:43:41.419
I opened up his hand and
I put the 100 rupee note,

00:43:41.419 --> 00:43:43.639
and he just looked at it like that,

00:43:43.639 --> 00:43:46.431
and his hand began to quiver,

00:43:46.431 --> 00:43:49.264
and he said sob ge, respected sir.

00:43:50.823 --> 00:43:53.788
(speaking foreign language)

00:43:53.788 --> 00:43:56.187
May God richly bless you.

00:43:56.187 --> 00:44:00.354
It's the greatest benediction
I have ever received.

00:44:01.515 --> 00:44:04.320
Bless people, let them see it.

00:44:04.320 --> 00:44:06.675
It's an apologetic, not
merely heard but seen.

00:44:06.675 --> 00:44:10.902
Secondly, not merely argued
but also felt in conviction.

00:44:10.902 --> 00:44:13.379
Not merely argued but also
felt in in conviction.

00:44:13.379 --> 00:44:15.899
Here I say, pray for wisdom.

00:44:15.899 --> 00:44:17.295
Please pray for wisdom.

00:44:17.295 --> 00:44:20.175
How to disarm an antagonist.

00:44:20.175 --> 00:44:22.887
(mumbles) I have 46 other apologists

00:44:22.887 --> 00:44:25.559
working with me on our
team and 15 countries.

00:44:25.559 --> 00:44:28.827
I keep talking to them, be humble in heart

00:44:28.827 --> 00:44:30.378
and be wise in wise in response.

00:44:30.378 --> 00:44:32.280
Humble in heart, wise in response.

00:44:32.280 --> 00:44:35.197
So you're not answering a question,

00:44:36.323 --> 00:44:38.297
you're answering a questioner.

00:44:38.297 --> 00:44:39.695
You're not answering a question,

00:44:39.695 --> 00:44:42.294
you're answering a questioner,

00:44:42.294 --> 00:44:45.093
and it reminded me of the
time I was in the middle east.

00:44:45.093 --> 00:44:47.692
Quick story and final thought,

00:44:47.692 --> 00:44:51.215
and we were talking to one of
the four founders of Hamas,

00:44:51.215 --> 00:44:53.255
muscle bound guy.

00:44:53.255 --> 00:44:55.295
The archbishop of
Canterbury took five of us.

00:44:55.295 --> 00:44:58.131
We're meeting with Israeli
leaders and Palestinian leaders

00:44:58.131 --> 00:44:59.751
and boy this guy was hostile.

00:44:59.751 --> 00:45:01.191
He spent years in prison.

00:45:01.191 --> 00:45:02.571
You could barely get a word in,

00:45:02.571 --> 00:45:04.190
he was so argumentative.

00:45:04.190 --> 00:45:06.351
His room was full of tobacco smoke,

00:45:06.351 --> 00:45:08.602
and after about several hours,

00:45:08.602 --> 00:45:10.740
the archbishop said to the five of us,

00:45:10.740 --> 00:45:12.768
would each one of you men
like to ask one question?

00:45:12.768 --> 00:45:14.296
So I asked mine.

00:45:14.296 --> 00:45:15.508
I won't tell you the question,

00:45:15.508 --> 00:45:16.858
this was a private conversation,

00:45:16.858 --> 00:45:20.456
but I can tell you this,
I didn't like his answer,

00:45:20.456 --> 00:45:21.781
and so I looked at him and I said,

00:45:21.781 --> 00:45:24.840
"Sir, I really don't like your answer.

00:45:24.840 --> 00:45:26.596
"I have to be honest with you."

00:45:26.596 --> 00:45:28.276
I said, "Can I tell you something?

00:45:28.276 --> 00:45:30.132
"Not far from where you and I are sitting,

00:45:30.132 --> 00:45:32.744
"5,000 years ago a man
by the name of Abraham

00:45:32.744 --> 00:45:34.904
"took his son up the hill
and was gonna offer him

00:45:34.904 --> 00:45:36.136
"as a sacrifice."

00:45:36.136 --> 00:45:37.500
I said, "You remember the story?"

00:45:37.500 --> 00:45:38.333
He said yes.

00:45:38.333 --> 00:45:40.121
I said, "Please let's
not debate which son,

00:45:40.121 --> 00:45:42.436
"let's just agree he
took his son up that hill

00:45:42.436 --> 00:45:44.340
"to offer him as a sacrifice."

00:45:44.340 --> 00:45:45.839
He said, "That's right."

00:45:45.839 --> 00:45:47.744
I said, "As the ax about to come down,

00:45:47.744 --> 00:45:49.659
"God stops it, remember that?"

00:45:49.659 --> 00:45:50.604
He said, "Yes."

00:45:50.604 --> 00:45:52.398
I said, "What did God say?

00:45:52.398 --> 00:45:53.529
He didn't know.

00:45:53.529 --> 00:45:56.348
I said, "God said stop,
I myself will provide."

00:45:56.348 --> 00:45:58.104
He said, "That's right."

00:45:58.104 --> 00:46:00.040
Stop, I myself will provide.

00:46:00.040 --> 00:46:01.916
I said, "Very close to
where you and I are sitting

00:46:01.916 --> 00:46:03.664
"in Rumula is another hill.

00:46:03.664 --> 00:46:06.804
"2,000 years ago God took
his own son up that hill,

00:46:06.804 --> 00:46:09.804
"and this time the ax did not stop."

00:46:11.395 --> 00:46:13.145
He just stared at me.

00:46:14.124 --> 00:46:17.737
I said, "Shaykh, until
you and I receive the son

00:46:17.737 --> 00:46:20.408
"God has provide, we'll
be offering our own sons

00:46:20.408 --> 00:46:22.448
"and daughters on the
battle fields of this world

00:46:22.448 --> 00:46:26.615
"for position, and power,
and land, and prestige."

00:46:28.387 --> 00:46:30.984
I myself got shocked that I said that.

00:46:30.984 --> 00:46:32.544
(laughing)

00:46:32.544 --> 00:46:34.012
I've never thought of it before.

00:46:34.012 --> 00:46:35.845
Leave alone saying it.

00:46:37.221 --> 00:46:38.424
And so the archbishop says,

00:46:38.424 --> 00:46:40.972
well you know I guess it's time to go now.

00:46:40.972 --> 00:46:42.728
(laughing)

00:46:42.728 --> 00:46:44.225
So we left.

00:46:44.225 --> 00:46:46.900
I thought boy I have blown this big time,

00:46:46.900 --> 00:46:48.984
and as I was walking I
felt this arm around me,

00:46:48.984 --> 00:46:50.200
and it was the archbishop.

00:46:50.200 --> 00:46:52.317
He leaned over and said,
"Ravi that was of God"

00:46:52.317 --> 00:46:54.468
I said, "I sure hope so."

00:46:54.468 --> 00:46:56.320
I don't know what I said.

00:46:56.320 --> 00:46:58.344
So we went down the steps,

00:46:58.344 --> 00:46:59.961
and the archbishop is the guest of honor.

00:46:59.961 --> 00:47:01.132
They were ushering him in.

00:47:01.132 --> 00:47:02.304
So the five of us are going.

00:47:02.304 --> 00:47:03.876
I'm still in a daze whether in the body

00:47:03.876 --> 00:47:05.871
or out of the body, I couldn't tell,

00:47:05.871 --> 00:47:08.064
and I hear somebody running behind me

00:47:08.064 --> 00:47:09.880
and he comes and twirls me around.

00:47:09.880 --> 00:47:11.241
It's the Shaykh.

00:47:11.241 --> 00:47:14.064
I said that's it I'm gonna
be buried here in (mumbles)

00:47:14.064 --> 00:47:18.485
it's over, this guy can
have me for dinner tonight,

00:47:18.485 --> 00:47:21.751
and then he looked at me and
stared me eye ball to eye ball

00:47:21.751 --> 00:47:24.228
holding onto my shoulders,

00:47:24.228 --> 00:47:26.732
and then he patted me on
both sides of the face.

00:47:26.732 --> 00:47:28.470
He said, "Mr. Zacharias."

00:47:28.470 --> 00:47:30.053
I said, "Yes, sir?"

00:47:31.772 --> 00:47:34.189
He said, "You are a good man.

00:47:36.468 --> 00:47:38.051
"You're a good man.

00:47:39.332 --> 00:47:42.108
I hope I will see you again someday."

00:47:42.108 --> 00:47:45.335
And he gave a big solid bear hug,

00:47:45.335 --> 00:47:47.280
and as he pulled himself away

00:47:47.280 --> 00:47:52.228
I looked at his eyes and
he's wiping the tears off.

00:47:52.228 --> 00:47:55.957
I don't know what happened following.

00:47:55.957 --> 00:47:58.136
I've never been back
to be able to see him.

00:47:58.136 --> 00:48:00.845
I'm watched carefully when I go there,

00:48:00.845 --> 00:48:04.095
but a word in season can bring to fruit

00:48:05.380 --> 00:48:08.243
that which only God can
nurture and nourish,

00:48:08.243 --> 00:48:11.668
and I say to you, ask God for wisdom.

00:48:11.668 --> 00:48:13.409
We're not picking a fight,

00:48:13.409 --> 00:48:16.560
we're looking for answers
that'll break through the course

00:48:16.560 --> 00:48:18.960
resistance and do it in love.

00:48:18.960 --> 00:48:20.377
Set apart Christ.

00:48:21.768 --> 00:48:23.911
It's not merely heard but seen.

00:48:23.911 --> 00:48:26.148
Not merely argued but also felt,

00:48:26.148 --> 00:48:29.032
and lastly we cannot only rescue the ends

00:48:29.032 --> 00:48:31.053
of bringing them to Christ.

00:48:31.053 --> 00:48:35.136
We must rescue the means
of the very word of God.

00:48:36.217 --> 00:48:38.518
Let me tell you something.

00:48:38.518 --> 00:48:42.855
What is it the gospel gives
that no other world view gives?

00:48:42.855 --> 00:48:45.193
Think about this question.

00:48:45.193 --> 00:48:48.526
It gives you an awful lot, an awful lot.

00:48:50.336 --> 00:48:52.860
In fact, I preached a message last week

00:48:52.860 --> 00:48:55.288
