00:49:46.979 --> 00:49:49.637
I said, "May I quote you
on that Shaykh Hussein?"

00:49:49.637 --> 00:49:51.304
He said, "Yes, why?"

00:49:52.636 --> 00:49:56.386
Some years ago I was in
San Juan, Puerto Rico

00:49:59.079 --> 00:50:01.447
and I was preaching at
a large church there,

00:50:01.447 --> 00:50:04.264
and the pastor was a man by
the name of Carmela Teranova.

00:50:04.264 --> 00:50:07.687
Great preacher, and I was in his office

00:50:07.687 --> 00:50:09.623
getting ready to go into the platform

00:50:09.623 --> 00:50:12.143
and I saw a big painting in his office.

00:50:12.143 --> 00:50:16.074
It was a sweet little girl
sitting on the lap of our lord

00:50:16.074 --> 00:50:19.282
holding his hand and looking at it,

00:50:19.282 --> 00:50:23.449
and the words in Spanish said,
what happened to your hands?

00:50:28.834 --> 00:50:31.167
What happened to your hands?

00:50:36.544 --> 00:50:40.179
You know what happened to his hands?

00:50:40.179 --> 00:50:43.679
It what was here that wounded those hands,

00:50:45.459 --> 00:50:47.287
and that's why the hymn writer says,

00:50:47.287 --> 00:50:51.175
what language shall I borrow
to thank your dearest friend

00:50:51.175 --> 00:50:54.547
for this thy dying sorrow,
thy pity without end,

00:50:54.547 --> 00:50:58.479
oh make me thine forever
and should I fainting be,

00:50:58.479 --> 00:51:02.562
lord let me never never
outlive my love for thee.

